From: Zumeng Chen <zumeng.chen@windriver.com>
Date: Fri, 1 Nov 2013 11:09:37 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 44/44] NFC: disable flooded kernel info when transfer

It is uncessary to see information about each NFC transfer, so
we can change log level to debug. This cleans up the logs, but
maintains the information for debugging purposes.

Signed-off-by: Zumeng Chen <zumeng.chen@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/nfc/pn544/pn544.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/nfc/pn544/pn544.c b/drivers/nfc/pn544/pn544.c
index b5048cb..07f4d1a6 100644
--- a/drivers/nfc/pn544/pn544.c
+++ b/drivers/nfc/pn544/pn544.c
@@ -618,7 +618,7 @@ static int pn544_hci_im_transceive(struct nfc_hci_dev *hdev,
 {
 	struct pn544_hci_info *info = nfc_hci_get_clientdata(hdev);
 
-	pr_info(DRIVER_DESC ": %s for gate=%d\n", __func__,
+	pr_debug(DRIVER_DESC ": %s for gate=%d\n", __func__,
 		target->hci_reader_gate);
 
 	switch (target->hci_reader_gate) {
